    <stitle>5 SPEED AND 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - REMOVE - COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="7">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When the rear bearing cover is removed, the countershaft may slide to the rear and out of the
                    bearing bore.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear bearing bolts, cover and shims (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302629">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302629" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302629" filename="../figg13/G1302629.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 29. Remove Rear Bearing Bolts, Cover and Shims</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft rear bearing cup (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302630">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302630" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302630" filename="../figg13/G1302630.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Remove Countershaft Rear Bearing Cup</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the countershaft assembly to the rear and lift the assembly from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302631">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302631" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302631" filename="../figg13/G1302631.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. Move Countershaft Assembly to Rear and Lift From Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the countershaft front bearing race is to be replaced, drive the bore plug through the
                case front. Drive the race rearward through the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302632">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302632" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302632" filename="../figg13/G1302632.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Drive Bore Plug Through Case Front</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the plug snap ring. Remove if damaged (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302633">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302633" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302633" filename="../figg13/G1302633.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Inspect Plug Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the transmission oil fill plug and the drain plug from the transmission case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302634">Figure 34</hotlnk>)
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302634" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302634" filename="../figg13/G1302634.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 34. Remove Transmission Oil Fill Plug and Drain Plug</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the oil fill plug and drain plug for damage (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302635">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302635" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302635" filename="../figg13/G1302635.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 35. Inspect Oil Fill Plug and Drain Plug</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
